1. Information We Collect
We and our third-party partners collect information about you and your use of the HyperBeard General Audience Games.
Most of this data comes directly from you or your device, such as device information, your country and region, and game play information.
The information we collect falls into three categories: (1) information collected directly from you; (2) information collected automatically, and (3) information collected from third parties.
(1) information collected directly from you
When you download our game, we may collect your name or other identifiers you provide.
If you subscribe to our newsletter, we collect your email.
If you communicate with our customer service team via email or via our Zendesk website, we collect information you submit in the course of that communication, such as your contact information, the contents of emails you send us, support inquiries, or other feedback you provide directly to us.
Information you provide in game reviews and surveys.
Registration information, including a username and password.
Purchase information, such as quantity and type of goods purchased, name of purchaser, and shipping address. If you make in-app purchases, we collect your ZIP code or postal code and information regarding your virtual items or currency in the HyperBeard General Audience Games, including the amount of the transaction and records of purchases you have made. Additional information about these transactions is provided in the “In-App Purchases” section below.
Payment information for your purchase, which is processed by our third-party payment processor.
If you communicate with HyperBeard through our presence on third party platforms such as Facebook, Twitter, or Discord, we collect information about the communication, such as your “liking” of our page, content of your comments, or replies to our content.
Marketing preferences, such as records of your requests to opt out of marketing communications.
(2) information collected automatically
We use in-app analytical tools to collect unique user ID, IP address, device IDs, hardware or operating system based identifiers, identifiers we assign to your account, and other similar identifiers (collected from your device).
Information on your activity in the HyperBeard General Audience Game (for example, your game progress or your interactions with in-game ads), Internet, gaming, or other electronic network activity information – such as information regarding your interaction with an advertisement (collected from your device).  Your gameplay records are stored in the cloud if you opt-in to Cloud Save on some games. In other games it is stored locally on your device depending on the ability to provide such an option by the Apple & Google Play platforms.
Your general geographic location (for example, country, state, or city), determined based on your IP address.
(3) information collected from third parties
HyperBeard collects user information through the third-party advertising networks on HyperBeard General Audience Games. This information includes your device ID, a unique advertising ID associated with your device, and your approximate geographic location. For more information, see the “Advertising” subsection below.
If you use a third-party platform to connect with HyperBeard General Audience Games, we collect third-party platform account information and information made public in connection with that service (including your name, profile picture, age range, gender, and your friends). Please keep in mind that when you post information on a third-party site or platform, the information you provide may be separately collected by the third-party site or platform. The information we collect is covered by this privacy policy and the information the third-party site or platform collects is subject to the third-party site or platform’s privacy practices. Privacy choices you have made on the third-party site or platform will not apply to our use of the information we have collected directly through the HyperBeard General Audience Game.
2. How We Use Your Information
HyperBeard will use your information for the following purposes:
To provide you with the products and services you request, including to provide the HyperBeard General Audience Games.
To operate, administer, and troubleshoot the HyperBeard General Audience Games.
To analyze usage patterns and performance of the HyperBeard General Audience Games.
To fulfill your orders.
To advertise to you, as described in the “Advertising” subsection below.
To provide you with customer support.
To send you newsletters or product updates by email if you have subscribed to our newsletter.
To send you notifications about real-time updates, transactional messages, and reminders.
To allow you to log in to HyperBeard General Audience Games on multiple devices via Cloud Save.
To contact you with updates about HyperBeard General Audience Games (if you have subscribed to our newsletter).
To administer surveys, sweepstakes, special promotions and contests.
To determine what rights you have with respect to your data under applicable law.
To comply with applicable laws and regulations, including to detect, investigate, and prevent activities that may violate our policies or be illegal.
To enforce the legal or contractual terms that govern your use of the HyperBeard General Audience Games or defend our legal rights.
In addition, HyperBeard may use your information for the following purposes because these purposes are in HyperBeard’s legitimate business interests:
To optimize or improve our products, services, and operations.
To improve the HyperBeard General Audience Games and user experiences and to increase the functionality of the HyperBeard General Audience Games.
To monitor and analyze the HyperBeard General Audience Games usage and trends and otherwise measure the effectiveness of the services.
HyperBeard may also combine information that we collect from you with information we obtain about you from third parties. We may aggregate and/or de-identify any information collected through the HyperBeard General Audience Games. We may use de-identified and/or aggregated data for any purpose, including without limitation for research and marketing purposes, and may also disclose such data to any third parties.
3. How We Disclose Your Information
We may disclose your information in the following circumstances:
At your direction, such as directing us to disclose your information with third-party sites or platforms, such as social networking sites, or when you write a review.
When we contract or partner with a third party to provide services, including HyperBeard General Audience Games development and maintenance. These parties provide a variety of services, including, without limitation, order processing, billing, sales, marketing, advertising, market research, fulfillment, data storage, analysis and processing, and legal services.
When we disclose information with third parties in connection with the sale, merger, or reorganization of all or part of the HyperBeard business.
To enforce our Terms of Use or rules, to ensure the safety and security of our users and third parties, to protect our rights and property and the rights and property of our users and third parties, address issues relating to security or fraud, to comply with legal process or in other cases if we believe in good faith that disclosure is required by law.
As described in the “Analytics and Advertising” section below.
Please note that once we disclose your information with another company in any of the circumstances set out above, the information received by the other company becomes subject to the other company’s privacy practices. However, when companies perform services on our behalf as service providers, like customer service, we have agreements with those companies that govern their data practices and prohibit them from using your information for purposes other than those requested by us or required by law.
4. Analytics and Advertising
Analytics
We may use third-party web analytics services on our HyperBeard General Audience Games to collect and analyze usage information through cookies and similar tools; engage in auditing, research, or reporting; assist with fraud prevention; and provide certain features to you. To prevent us from using your information for analytics, you may contact us as set forth in the “Your Controls and Choices” information below. If you’d like to opt out of Google Analytics, please use the Google Analytics Opt-Out Browser Add-on located here:
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
. Because opt out requests are tied to your device ID, please note that you will need to opt out on each device you use to access the HyperBeard General Audience Games.
If you receive email from us, we may use certain analytics tools, such as clear GIFs to capture data such as when you open our message or click on any links or banners our email contains. This data allows us to gauge the effectiveness of our communications and marketing campaigns.
Advertising
HyperBeard relies on advertising to fund the development and distribution of the HyperBeard Games, most of which are available to play at no cost to you.  Accordingly, when you play the HyperBeard General Audience Games you may see third-party advertising.  This advertising is delivered to the HyperBeard General Audience Games by advertising networks that sell advertising to interested third parties.  Advertising networks collect a unique device ID or advertising ID (Apple Identifier for Advertisers (“IDFA”) on Apple devices and Google Advertising Identity (“GAID”) on Android devices) that enables the delivery of advertisements that are relevant to you.  Your advertising ID is consistent across all apps and thus allows for cross-app tracking and interest-based advertising.  Advertising IDs are non-permanent, non-personal identifiers uniquely associated with your device.  Similar technologies include tracking pixels within ads.  These technologies allow companies (including marketers and advertisers) to recognize your device when you use websites and applications.  Advertising networks may use your device’s IP address to determine your approximate geographic location to enable them to deliver more relevant advertisements.
If you engage with our General Audience Games via your mobile device, you may be able to limit advertising through your device settings. Please see your device manufacturer’s instructions for more information.
Please also see the “Your Controls and Choices” section, below, for more information on other ways you may limit analytics and targeted advertising.
5. In-App Purchases and Rewards
Certain HyperBeard General Audience Games may allow you to make In-App Purchases.  All In-App Purchases are processed by third party payment processors that may collect information directly from you (for example, they may request your billing address and credit card information) in accordance with its own privacy policy.  HyperBeard’s third party payment processors do not disclose your financial information, like credit card number, with HyperBeard.  We receive summary information about all purchases, including the amount of the transaction and your general location (such as your ZIP code).
Some HyperBeard General Audience Games reward you with in-game currency (such as coins or gems) for watching advertisements. If you are a California resident, please review the Incentive Program section in
Appendix A
.
6. Your Controls and Choices
In accordance with applicable law, you may be able to request to exercise certain rights with respect to the information we hold about you.  You may request to exercise your controls and choices by contacting
legal@hyperbeard.com
.
