Activities to verify or maintain the quality or safety of our services, and to improve, upgrade, or enhance our services.
What Personal Information We “Sell” and “Share”
We primarily collect, use, and disclose de-identified and/or aggregated consumer information, which is not considered personal information under CCPA since it does not directly or indirectly reveal your identity.  However, CCPA defines “sale” and “share” broadly to include the sharing of CCPA Covered Information (by a covered business) in exchange for anything of value or for cross contextual behavioral advertising purposes, and enabling third-party ad networks and advertising partners to collect CCPA Covered Information for these purposes.  According to this broad definition, in the year before the date this policy was issued, for some HyperBeard General Audience Games we collected, and may have sold or shared:
Unique and online identifiers – IP address, device IDs, or other similar identifiers (collected from your device);
Internet, gaming, or other electronic network activity information – such as browsing history, search history, and information regarding an individual’s interaction with an internet website, application, or advertisement (collected from your device); and
Location information – for example, if you access our games on your mobile device our advertisers may derive information about location from your IP address.
We may disclose or permit collection of this information to/by recipients such as ad networks and other advertising partners to achieve these business purposes. This means that we may disclose the categories of personal information listed above for a business purpose.
Your Choices Regarding “Sharing” and “Selling”
:
You may have the right to opt out of our sale/sharing of your personal information for purposes of online analytics and advertising. To opt out of the disclosure of your personal information for these purposes within a HyperBeard General Audience Game, click the “Your Privacy Choices” link within the specific HyperBeard General Audience Game you are using (you need to repeat this choice for each HyperBeard General Audience Game) and follow the prompts. In some cases, you may be presented a toggle you can use to opt out. You may also exercise your opt out rights by contacting
legal@hyperbeard.com
.
Incentive Programs
The HyperBeard General Audience Games may offer opportunities to receive certain services or benefits such as discounts or free or extended services (such as bonus game time or additional credits), which may require the provision of personal information. Such opportunities could be considered a financial incentive under applicable law (each, an “Incentive Program”).  When you participate in an Incentive Program, you agree to the terms of that Incentive Program, and may revoke your participation depending on the Incentive Program (e.g., by opting out of emails or terminating a service). To the extent we can determine the value of your information, we consider the value to you (and costs to us) of providing you with a discount, as compared to the value to us in an opportunity to gain a loyal, or even more loyal, customer; we seek to reasonably relate the benefits to you to the costs to us.
Sensitive Personal Information
The CCPA also allows you to limit the use or disclosure of your “sensitive personal information” (as defined in the CCPA) if your sensitive personal information is used for certain purposes.   In the limited circumstances that we process sensitive personal information as defined in the CCPA (such as usernames in combination with passwords), we do not use or disclose it other than for disclosed and permitted business purposes for which there is not a right to limit under the CCPA.
Please see the “Your Controls And Your Choices” section of our Policy above for information about the additional rights you have with respect to your personal information under California law and how to exercise them.
Retention of Your Personal Information
. Please see the “Data Retention” section above.
How to Exercise Your Rights
If you are a California resident to whom the CCPA applies, you may exercise your rights, if any, by contacting us at
legal@hyperbeard.com
.
